body:
I have a similar problem when running code to periodically gather windows titles and icons. Code looks like this in main process:

```
setInterval(async () => {
    const options: Electron.SourcesOptions = {
      types: ["window"],
      fetchWindowIcons: true,
    };

    getLogger().debug("Calling getSources");
    const sources = await desktopCapturer.getSources(options);
    getLogger().debug("Finished sources");
}, 10000);
```

After some minutes running, I can only see a lot of `"Calling getSources"` lines in log - i.e., the call does not resolve. Electron version is 11.3.0 (previously, with version 11.1.1, app would simply freeze after entering a `getSources` call, but after updating it does not make app freeze, but does not return either).

Ps: platform in this case in Windows. Should I open a separate issue? Behavior seems the same as the one described here.

Electron returns the same Promise object if two successive calls to `getSources` are made with equal arguments. So if one fails, others will subsequently fail too. While this bug isn't solved, a possible workaround is to add an extra field to the `thumbnailSize`, inside the `options` argument, so that electron does not return same old Promise and actually runs the `getSources` logic again:


```diff
const { app, desktopCapturer, screen } = require('electron');

const fs = require('fs')
const path = require('path')


function takeScreenshot() {
    console.log('Gathering screens...');
    const thumbSize = determineScreenShotSize();
+    const workaroundTimestamp = Date.now();
-     const options = { types: ['screen'], thumbnailSize: thumbSize }
+    const options = {
+                       types: ['screen'],
+                       thumbnailSize: { ...thumbSize, workaroundTimestamp} 
+                    };

    desktopCapturer.getSources(options).then((sources) => {
        console.log('Sources received:'+sources.length);
        sources.forEach(function (source) {
            const sourceName = source.name.toLowerCase();
            console.log(sourceName);
            if ( ['entire screen', 'screen 1'].includes(sourceName)) {
                const screenshotPath = path.join(app.getPath('pictures'), 'screenshot-' + new Date().toJSON() + '.png')
                fs.writeFile(screenshotPath, source.thumbnail.toPNG(), function (error) {
                    if (error) return console.log(error)
                    console.log('Saved screenshot to: ' + screenshotPath);
                })
            }
        })
    }).catch(console.error);
}

function determineScreenShotSize() {
    var screenSize = screen.getPrimaryDisplay().workAreaSize
    return {
        width: screenSize.width,
        height: screenSize.height
    }
}
setInterval(takeScreenshot, 15000);
```
